{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848804810,"sessionID":"ses_2872adc5dffeM4vfQ7QpP2w1um","part":{"id":"prt_d78d651a0001U7hEat5EL7JaZ4","messageID":"msg_d78d5875a001pDIK41AiUtkVIl","sessionID":"ses_2872adc5dffeM4vfQ7QpP2w1um","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-e915b05de4514cfba6d044b89fe824bd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-009 Design - Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core\n\n## Overview\n\nThe Router module provides HTTP reverse proxy capabilities for routing client requests to sandbox instances (AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter). It acts as the entry point for all external traffic, managing session-based routing, authentication, and request forwarding.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────┐\n│  Client Request │\n└────────┬────────┘\n         │\n         ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  HTTP Server (Gin)                  │\n│  - Request Validation               │\n│  - Concurrency Limiting             │\n│  - Logging/Recovery                 │\n└────────┬────────────────────────────┘\n         │\n         ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Router Handler                     │\n│  - Session Extraction               │\n│  - JWT Generation/Validation        │\n│  - Sandbox Lookup                   │\n└────────┬────────────────────────────┘\n         │\n         ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Session Manager                    │\n│  - Cache Lookup                     │\n│  - Workload Manager Call            │\n│  - Session Creation/Retrieval       │\n└────────┬────────────────────────────┘\n         │\n         ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Reverse Proxy                      │\n│  - Request Forwarding               │\n│  - Response Modification            │\n│  - Header Management                │\n└────────┬────────────────────────────┘\n         │\n         ▼\n┌─────────────────┐\n│  Sandbox Pod    │\n└─────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Layered Architecture\n\n1. **HTTP Layer**: Gin-based HTTP server with middleware\n2. **Routing Layer**: Request routing and session management\n3. **Proxy Layer**: HTTP reverse proxy with transport configuration\n4. **Integration Layer**: Store, JWT, and workload manager clients\n\n### Key Components\n\n#### Server (`server.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    config         *Config\n    engine         *gin.Engine\n    httpServer     *http.Server\n    sessionManager SessionManager\n    storeClient    store.Store\n    httpTransport  *http.Transport\n    jwtManager     *JWTManager\n}\n```\n\n**Responsibilities:**\n- HTTP server lifecycle management\n- Route registration and middleware setup\n- Graceful shutdown handling\n- Health check endpoints\n\n#### Session Manager (`session_manager.go`)\n\n```go\ntype SessionManager interface {\n    GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n\ntype manager struct {\n    storeClient     store.Store\n    workloadMgrAddr string\n    httpClient      *http.Client\n}\n```\n\n**Responsibilities:**\n- Session-based sandbox lookup\n- Cache integration for performance\n- Workload manager communication\n- Session validation\n\n#### JWT Manager (`jwt.go`)\n\n```go\ntype JWTManager struct {\n    privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n    publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n    clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n}\n```\n\n**Responsibilities:**\n- JWT token generation for sandbox authentication\n- RSA key pair generation and persistence\n- Kubernetes secret management for key storage\n- Token-based authentication for sandbox requests\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Configuration\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Port                  string\n    Debug                 bool\n    EnableTLS             bool\n    TLSCert               string\n    TLSKey                string\n    MaxConcurrentRequests int\n}\n```\n\n**Default Values:**\n- Port: \"8080\"\n- Debug: false\n- EnableTLS: false\n- TLSCert: \"\"\n- TLSKey: \"\"\n- MaxConcurrentRequests: 1000\n\n### Session Data\n\n```go\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    Kind             string              // \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n    SandboxID        string              // Unique sandbox identifier\n    SandboxName      string              // Pod name\n    SandboxNamespace string              // Pod namespace\n    Name             string              // Resource name\n    EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint // Available service endpoints\n    SessionID        string              // Session identifier\n    CreatedAt        time.Time           // Session creation time\n    ExpiresAt        time.Time           // Session expiration time\n    Status           string              // Sandbox status\n    PodIP            string              // Pod IP address\n    WorkloadName     string              // Workload name\n    Namespace        string              // Resource namespace\n    LastActivityAt   time.Time           // Last activity timestamp\n}\n```\n\n### Entry Point\n\n```go\ntype SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n    Path     string // URL path prefix\n    Protocol string // \"http\" or \"https\"\n    Endpoint string // Target URL endpoint\n}\n```\n\n### JWT Claims\n\n```go\ntype JWTClaims struct {\n    SessionID string `json:\"session_id\"`\n    jwt.RegisteredClaims\n}\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### HTTP Endpoints\n\n#### Health Checks\n\n**GET `/health/live`**\n- Purpose: Liveness probe for Kubernetes\n- Response: `{\"status\":\"alive\"}`\n- No authentication required\n\n**GET `/health/ready`**\n- Purpose: Readiness probe for Kubernetes\n- Response: `{\"status\":\"ready\"}` or `{\"status\":\"not ready\",\"error\":\"...\"}`\n- Checks session manager availability\n\n#### Agent Runtime Invocation\n\n**GET/POST `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path`**\n\n**Middleware:**\n1. `gin.Logger()` - Request logging\n2. `gin.Recovery()` - Panic recovery\n3. `concurrencyLimitMiddleware` - Concurrency control\n\n**Path Parameters:**\n- `namespace`: Kubernetes namespace\n- `name`: AgentRuntime resource name\n- `path`: Request path to forward to sandbox\n\n**Flow:**\n1. Extract or generate session ID from request\n2. Validate session and retrieve sandbox info\n3. Generate JWT token for authentication\n4. Reverse proxy request to sandbox endpoint\n5. Add `x-agentcube-session-id` header to response\n\n**Success Response:** Proxied sandbox response\n\n**Error Responses:**\n- 400: Invalid request parameters\n- 404: Sandbox not found\n- 429: Concurrency limit exceeded\n- 500: Internal server error\n\n#### Code Interpreter Invocation\n\n**GET/POST `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path`**\n\nSame flow and error handling as Agent Runtime invocation.\n\n### Workload Manager API\n\n**Create Sandbox**\n- Method: POST\n- Endpoint: `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/agent-runtime` or `/v1/code-interpreter`\n- Request Body: `CreateSandboxRequest`\n- Response Body: `CreateSandboxResponse`\n\n**Get Session**\n- Method: GET\n- Endpoint: `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/session/{sessionID}`\n- Response Body: `GetSessionResponse`\n\n### Store Interface\n\nThe router uses the `store.Store` interface for caching session data:\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    Get(ctx context.Context, key string) ([]byte, error)\n    Set(ctx context.Context, key string, value []byte, ttl time.Duration) error\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, key string) error\n}\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Types\n\n1. **Validation Errors** (400)\n   - Invalid resource kind\n   - Missing required parameters\n   - Invalid session ID format\n\n2. **Not Found Errors** (404)\n   - AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter resource not found\n   - Session not found\n   - Sandbox pod not available\n\n3. **Concurrency Limit Errors** (429)\n   - Maximum concurrent requests exceeded\n   - Server under heavy load\n\n4. **Internal Server Errors** (500)\n   - Workload manager communication failures\n   - Store access failures\n   - Proxy transport errors\n   - JWT generation failures\n\n### Error Response Format\n\n```go\ntype ErrorResponse struct {\n    Error string `json:\"error\"`\n    Code  string `json:\"code,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Example:**\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"sandbox not found\",\n  \"code\": \"SANDBOX_NOT_FOUND\"\n}\n```\n\n### Error Handling Strategy\n\n1. **Graceful Degradation**\n   - Return cached sandbox info if workload manager is temporarily unavailable\n   - Continue serving requests during partial failures\n\n2. **Circuit Breaker Pattern**\n   - Limit retries to workload manager\n   - Fail fast after consecutive failures\n   - Automatic recovery after timeout\n\n3. **Context Cancellation**\n   - Propagate context timeouts to downstream calls\n   - Clean up resources on cancellation\n   - Respect client deadlines\n\n4. **Logging**\n   - Log all errors with structured fields\n   - Include request correlation IDs\n   - Aggregate error metrics\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### Server Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestNewServer(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestServer_Start(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestServer_Shutdown(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**Coverage:**\n- Server initialization\n- Graceful shutdown\n- Configuration validation\n\n#### Session Manager Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionManager_cacheHit(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionManager_cacheMiss(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionManager_workloadManagerCall(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**Coverage:**\n- Cache hit scenarios\n- Cache miss scenarios\n- Workload manager communication\n- Error handling\n\n#### JWT Manager Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestJWTManager_GenerateToken(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestJWTManager_TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestJWTManager_keyRotation(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**Coverage:**\n- Token generation and validation\n- RSA key generation\n- Secret persistence\n- Key rotation scenarios\n\n#### Handler Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestHandleHealthLive(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestHandleHealthReady(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestHandleAgentInvoke(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestHandleCodeInterpreterInvoke(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**Coverage:**\n- Request handling\n- Parameter extraction\n- Response formatting\n- Error cases\n\n#### Middleware Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestConcurrencyLimitMiddleware(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestConcurrencyLimitMiddleware_exceeded(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**Coverage:**\n- Concurrency control\n- Rate limiting\n- Headers and status codes\n\n#### Proxy Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestReverseProxy_Forwarding(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestReverseProxy_HeaderModification(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestReverseProxy_Transport(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**Coverage:**\n- Request forwarding\n- Header manipulation\n- Response modification\n- Transport configuration\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n#### End-to-End Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestE2E_AgentRuntimeInvocation(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestE2E_CodeInterpreterInvocation(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestE2E_SessionLifecycle(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestE2E_ErrorScenarios(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**Setup:**\n- Mock workload manager server\n- In-memory store\n- Test AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter resources\n\n**Coverage:**\n- Complete request flow\n- Session creation and reuse\n- Error propagation\n- Performance characteristics\n\n#### Store Integration Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestStoreIntegration_SessionCaching(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestStoreIntegration_TTLExpiration(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**Coverage:**\n- Store operations\n- TTL behavior\n- Concurrent access\n\n### Performance Tests\n\n```go\nfunc BenchmarkHandleAgentInvoke(b *testing.B)\nfunc BenchmarkHandleCodeInterpreterInvoke(b *testing.B)\nfunc BenchmarkConcurrencyLimitMiddleware(b *testing.B)\nfunc BenchmarkReverseProxy(b *testing.B)\n```\n\n**Metrics:**\n- Request throughput\n- Latency percentiles\n- Memory usage\n- Goroutine count\n\n### Load Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestLoad_ConcurrentRequests(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestLoad_LongRunningRequests(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestLoad_MixedWorkload(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**Scenarios:**\n- Concurrent request handling\n- Memory pressure\n- Connection pooling\n- Backlog management\n\n### Security Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestSecurity_JWTValidation(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSecurity_PathTraversal(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSecurity_HeaderInjection(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSecurity_TLSConfiguration(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**Coverage:**\n- Authentication bypass attempts\n- Input validation\n- Header manipulation\n- TLS certificate handling\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Authentication\n\n1. **JWT-based Authentication**\n   - RSA 2048-bit keys\n   - RS256 signing algorithm\n   - 5-minute token expiration\n   - Key rotation support\n\n2. **Secret Management**\n   - Kubernetes secrets for key storage\n   - In-cluster service account tokens\n   - Secure key generation\n\n### Authorization\n\n1. **Namespace Isolation**\n   - Requests scoped to specific namespace\n   - Cross-namespace access prevention\n\n2. **Resource Access Control**\n   - Resource name validation\n   - Kind-based routing\n\n### Transport Security\n\n1. **TLS Support**\n   - Optional TLS termination\n   - Certificate validation\n   - Secure cipher suites\n\n2. **HTTP/2 Support**\n   - HTTP/2 transport configuration\n   - Connection pooling\n   - Multiplexing\n\n### Input Validation\n\n1. **Path Sanitization**\n   - Path traversal prevention\n   - URL normalization\n   - Reserved path handling\n\n2. **Parameter Validation**\n   - Namespace validation\n   - Resource name validation\n   - Session ID validation\n\n### Rate Limiting\n\n1. **Concurrency Control**\n   - Configurable concurrency limits\n   - 429 responses on limit exceeded\n   - Backpressure management\n\n## Performance Optimizations\n\n### Caching\n\n1. **Session Caching**\n   - Store-based cache\n   - Configurable TTL\n   - Cache invalidation\n\n2. **Connection Pooling**\n   - HTTP/2 transport\n   - Keep-alive connections\n   - Connection reuse\n\n### Request Processing\n\n1. **Streaming**\n   - Response streaming\n   - Chunked encoding\n   - No buffering\n\n2. **Zero-Copy**\n   - Efficient proxy forwarding\n   - Minimal request modification\n   - Low overhead\n\n### Resource Management\n\n1. **Goroutine Pooling**\n   - Bounded concurrency\n   - Worker pool pattern\n   - Context cancellation\n\n2. **Memory Management**\n   - Buffer pooling\n   - Memory reuse\n   - Garbage collection optimization\n\n## Monitoring and Observability\n\n### Metrics\n\n1. **HTTP Metrics**\n   - Request count\n   - Response time\n   - Error rate\n   - Active connections\n\n2. **Proxy Metrics**\n   - Proxy requests\n   - Backend latency\n   - Proxy errors\n\n3. **Session Metrics**\n   - Active sessions\n   - Cache hits/misses\n   - Session creation rate\n\n### Logging\n\n1. **Structured Logging**\n   - Request correlation IDs\n   - Session IDs\n   - Error stack traces\n   - Performance data\n\n2. **Log Levels**\n   - Debug: Detailed request/response\n   - Info: Key events and errors\n   - Error: Failure conditions\n   - Fatal: Critical failures\n\n### Tracing\n\n1. **Distributed Tracing**\n   - Request tracing\n   - Span propagation\n   - Performance profiling\n\n### Health Checks\n\n1. **Liveness Probe**\n   - HTTP endpoint `/health/live`\n   - Basic server health\n\n2. **Readiness Probe**\n   - HTTP endpoint `/health/ready`\n   - Dependency health checks\n\n## Deployment\n\n### Configuration\n\n**Environment Variables:**\n- `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`: Workload manager endpoint (required)\n- `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE`: Router namespace (default: `default`)\n\n**CLI Flags:**\n- `-port`: Server port (default: 8080)\n- `-enable-tls`: Enable TLS (default: false)\n- `-tls-cert`: TLS certificate path\n- `-tls-key`: TLS key path\n- `-debug`: Debug mode (default: false)\n- `-max-concurrent-requests`: Max concurrent requests (default: 1000)\n\n### Kubernetes Deployment\n\n**Deployment Manifest:**\n```yaml\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: Deployment\nmetadata:\n  name: agentcube-router\nspec:\n  replicas: 3\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: agentcube-router\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      labels:\n        app: agentcube-router\n    spec:\n      containers:\n      - name: router\n        image: volcano-sh/agentcube-router:latest\n        ports:\n        - containerPort: 8080\n        env:\n        - name: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n          value: \"http://agentcube-workload-manager:8081\"\n        - name: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n          value: \"default\"\n        livenessProbe:\n          httpGet:\n            path: /health/live\n            port: 8080\n        readinessProbe:\n          httpGet:\n            path: /health/ready\n            port: 8080\n```\n\n**Service Manifest:**\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: agentcube-router\nspec:\n  selector:\n    app: agentcube-router\n  ports:\n  - port: 80\n    targetPort: 8080\n  type: LoadBalancer\n```\n\n### Scalability\n\n1. **Horizontal Scaling**\n   - Stateless design\n   - Shared session store\n   - Load balancer distribution\n\n2. **Vertical Scaling**\n   - Configurable concurrency limits\n   - Resource requests/limits\n   - Performance tuning\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n1. **WebSocket Support**\n   - Real-time communication\n   - Connection upgrades\n   - Session management\n\n2. **Advanced Routing**\n   - Weight-based routing\n   - A/B testing\n   - Canary deployments\n\n3. **Security Enhancements**\n   - Mutual TLS\n   - IP whitelisting\n   - Rate limiting per client\n\n4. **Performance Improvements**\n   - HTTP/3 support\n   - QUIC protocol\n   - Compression\n\n5. **Observability**\n   - Prometheus metrics\n   - Grafana dashboards\n   - Alerting rules\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Runtime Dependencies\n\n- `github.com/gin-gonic/gin`: HTTP framework\n- `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5`: JWT library\n- `golang.org/x/net/http2`: HTTP/2 support\n- `k8s.io/client-go`: Kubernetes client\n- `k8s.io/klog/v2`: Logging\n\n### Internal Dependencies\n\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`: Store interface\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`: Common types\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/api`: API types\n\n## References\n\n- [Gin Framework Documentation](https://gin-gonic.com/docs/)\n- [Kubernetes API Conventions](https://github.com/kubernetes/community/blob/master/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md)\n- [HTTP Reverse Proxy Design](https://github.com/golang/go/tree/master/src/net/http/httputil)\n- [JWT Best Practices](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc8725)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-009/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/gc/collector_test.go\">\nERROR [127:15] expected 1 expression\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/codeinterpreter.go\">\nERROR [63:7] undefined: statusConditionsEqual\nERROR [106:6] undefined: statusConditionsEqual\nERROR [173:2] declared and not used: logger\nERROR [242:5] undefined: podSpecsEqual\nERROR [267:29] undefined: convertEnvVars\nERROR [274:25] undefined: convertResources\nERROR [326:6] undefined: statusConditionsEqual\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/controller.go\">\nERROR [57:3] unknown field MetricsBindAddress in struct literal of type controllerruntime.Options\nERROR [58:3] unknown field Port in struct literal of type controllerruntime.Options\nERROR [62:3] unknown field SyncPeriod in struct literal of type controllerrun