tion/Retrieval       │\n38: └────────┬────────────────────────────┘\n39:          │\n40:          ▼\n41: ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n42: │  Reverse Proxy                      │\n43: │  - Request Forwarding               │\n44: │  - Response Modification            │\n45: │  - Header Management                │\n46: └────────┬────────────────────────────┘\n47:          │\n48:          ▼\n49: ┌─────────────────┐\n50: │  Sandbox Pod    │\n\n(Showing lines 1-50 of 759. Use offset=51 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-009 Design - Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core\n\n## Overview\n\nThe Router module provides HTTP reverse proxy capabilities for routing client requests to sandbox instances (AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter). It acts as the entry point for all external traffic, managing session-based routing, authentication, and request forwarding.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────┐\n│  Client Request │\n└────────┬────────┘\n         │\n         ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  HTTP Server (Gin)                  │\n│  - Request Validation               │\n│  - Concurrency Limiting             │","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-009/design.md","time":{"start":1775848807330,"end":1775848807351}}}}
